Despite searches by cabin crew on the United Airlines flight the phone wasn't found, even though both Alex and Emma remember him having it on the plane. 

They had arrived on the UA27 Newark- Birmingham and still think the device could be between their seats 23b and 23a.

Now, months later, they are making one last desperate appeal to anyone who might have come across it.

The couple have posted their plea on the UK's biggest online lost and found site Lostbox.co.uk - which has been responsible for reuniting people with hundreds of items every month.

